Package fr.cnrs.iees.graph

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DataEdge
    An Edge with read/write data contained in it, accessible as properties.
    DataNode
    A Node with read/write data contained in it, accessible as properties.
    DynamicGraph<N extends Node,E extends Edge>
    A mutable graph, with the possibility to add or remove Elements
    Edge
    The basic features any edge in any graph should have
    EdgeFactory
    An interface to give a Graph the ability to create Edges in an appropriate way. cf.
    Graph<N extends Node,E extends Edge>
    An immutable graph (no possibility to add or remove elements as it is now unrelated to List).
    GraphElement
    The base features common to Edges and Nodes of a graph.
    Matrix  
    MinimalGraph<N>
    An interface to represent the most generic properties of any graph.
    Node
    The basic features any Node in any graph should have
    NodeFactory
    An interface to give a Graph the ability to create Nodes in an appropriate way.
    ReadOnlyDataEdge
    An Edge with properties that can only be read, not set.
    ReadOnlyDataNode
    A Node with properties that can only be read, not set.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EdgeAdapter
    A base implementation of Edge with all the methods that should be universal in descendants
    GraphElementAdapter
    A base implementation of Element with the methods that should be universal in all descendants
    NodeAdapter
    A base implementation of Node with all the methods that should be universal in descendants
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Direction
    Directions of edges for directed graphs.
